Package: iLBA
Title: Information Loss Bounded Aggregation
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides tools for constructing aggregated frequency tables from
  microdata that are masked using the iLBA algorithm, especially in the presence
  of hierarchical variables. There is a growing demand - particularly in
  statistical agencies - for aggregated frequency tables, as users often request
  statistics for specific subsets of variables, including those with hierarchical
  structures. The iLBA algorithm offers a masking method that ensures safe
  public release by simultaneously controlling both disclosure risk and
  information loss. This package provides tools for generating full frequency
  tables from microdata, producing masked aggregated frequency tables using the
  iLBA algorithm, and retrieving masked counts for specific combinations of
  variables.
